01/02/2005
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Turkey's ruling Justice and Development Party (AKP) has obtained official observer status in the European People's Party (EPP), according to media reports in Brussels on Monday (31 January). 
The board of the centre-right EPP, which has the largest caucus at the European Parliament, decided to grant the status to AKP late last week.
In other news, Turkey officially took control of Kabul Airport in Afghanistan at a formal ceremony Monday. 
Turkey is also to assume command of the International Security Assistance Force in Afghanistan later this month. 
(EU Observer, NTV - 31/01/05)
